Diagnosis.
Large broadly oval species (body length 
4.5–5.1 mm
). Reticulation of elytra composed of shallowly impressed very large meshes. Ground colour of elytra dark, brownblackish; mediolateral spot present (
Fig. 17
). Apical part of median lobe relatively shorter, with dorsal side lightly curved, and short and hooked apex; in lateral view with dorsal side almost straight (
Fig. 35
).
